<br>
Second, I'm seeing a general pattern here and coming to a realization.<br>
<br>
I DOUBT ANYONE HERE WOULD ACTUALLY FORGIVE HAWKESTONE AND STOP FLAMING THEM IF THEY DID FESS UP AND APOLOGIZE.<br>
<br>
No one here has tried asking for an apology.  Jesus Christ.  It's a fuck up.  It's not like all of you have never fucked up before.  I'm sure Hawkestone has no regrets, and they shouldn't.  But I'm sure by now they'll also admit that they fucked up, not in their eyes, but in the server's eyes.  And you know why they haven't?  No one gives a shit if they do.  Who the hell do all of you bashing them think you are to give them no retribution.  I hope you realize you've blown this way out of proportion.  BUT...if that's how you want to be, here are some new rules Xev should follow:<br>
<br>
1) If you KS someone, you get guild removed.  Do it again, guild forsaken.  A third time, and we get to spit on you.<br>
<br>
2) If you can be blamed for someone else's death, guild remove.  Same punishments as previous rule.<br>
<br>
3) If you piss someone off, same.  In fact, if you fuck up or step out of line, even just once, the same rules apply.<br>
<br>
4) You're not allowed to apologize.  Anyone who breaks any of these rules 3 times gets a serverwide /ignore.  You will be forgotten, and when you get depressed and go home and cancel your account, we'll all laugh at you.  Then we'll burn your house down.<br>
<br>
