<br>
To be honest, reading the post you made to me, it really sounds like someone who got their feathers ruffled over assuming that they were being personally attacked.  There is no personal attack in there for you, Aerdor, in fact, the only thing that had anything at all to do with you was the fact that I opened with a quote from you and made a comment to it - a rational, well thought out comment that did no harm to you or what you said.  It was simply a different way of looking at it.<br>
<br>
While this is the rant board, and you're by all means permitted (even encouraged) to get your feathers ruffled by anything you want to, a little breather before you post might make you look a little less of an overzealous hot head, and rationality goes a long way to being taken seriously. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aerdor>Aerdor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#330000>(6/8/03 8:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I know</span><hr size=1> Zackov, I never said what HS did was an accident.  In fact, instead of bending the truth, you could point out that I said that what they did was on purpose, no regrets.  But they still fucked up.  I'm sure as hell they're not all sitting around going &quot;Woops, so THAT'S what happens when you awake sleeper.&quot;  On the other hand, I'm sure they're also not happy that they upset as many people as they did.  That's where they fucked up.  They looked at the consequences for them, and forgot to look at the consequences of their actions for EVERYONE else.  I'm sure they originally said what they said in spite of a certain few individuals, but I'm also sure as hell they didn't purposely walk up to ever new player to the game and say &quot;Heya, Newb.  I'm from Hawkestone.  Spit on me.  I fucked the last frontier up because I knew YOU would want to go there one day.&quot;  That's the accident they made.  They didn't look at the whole picture, and that's what they need to apologize for.  That's what hurt everyone's feelings (because you're probably not here  unless you're mad or have some feeling towards what they did), and that's what needs to be apologized for.  I'm sure they already realized that apologizing for awakening the sleeper is something they could never do.<br>
<br>
Aerdor Dewcatcher<br>
52nd druid<br>
