<br>
It has been brought to my attention that my name appears on Browneye's (Hawkestone's) roster.  Whether this is someone's lame idea of a joke, or just some random (and quite odd) mistake, let me make a few things perfectly clear.<br>
<br>
(1) I am not, nor will I ever, be a member of a guild as juvenile and greedy as these people (and I use the term people loosely).  I find what they did to be the single most selfish and childish act I have ever seen, and this goes beyond just the time I have spent playing EQ.  You got yourself wiped out, despised, and just messed up an aspect of Xev that many players took great pride in.  When I found out what happened, I tried to find out WHY?  WHY could a guild be so selfish?  WHY would they take it on themselves to make a sacrifice like this (and it was a sacrifice).  In the end, all I found out was that there was no reason.  They did it to piss everyone off, bravo... job well done.  Let me tell you, I was impressed.<br>
<br>
(2) Since I have been brought into this discussion, I will share with you my feelings.  The people I have talked to in Cockeye are probably the rudest most childish group of people I have ever had the displeasure of dealing with.  This was BEFORE the sleeper situation, but when I saw how they handled (and are handling) this mess, it only makes me think that they are complete pricks on purpose.  If you want to check me out, to validate my claims, I am Tibult (yes, out of Romeo and Juliet) and I am a proud member of Knights of Reverence.  Send me a tell, unless you are a Hawke Dick, in which case I want nothing to do with you.<br>
<br>
and finally <br>
(3)  If I WERE a member of Cockstone, I would /guildremove.  No lie, that was totally fucked up.  What gives you dick heads the right to break an agreement made by the founding guilds of the server?  I for one will take great pleasure if I can one day watch you get beat to death, then break <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>my own code</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and train your corpse till it decays ( I never train corpses...it is a matter of honor with me).  You can bet that I will have any member of Hawkecock on my ignore list, and will live in anticipation of watching you die, even if you join them AFTER this day.  I don't care, you are guilty by association as far as I am concerned.  The best thing that can happen to this guild is that it dissolve and gather under a new name.  At least then we would have to learn who you are all over again... but then again, as we notice the names, you will be ratted out all over again.<br>
There is no hope for any of you.  Your stigma will carry to any guild you join, and the tale of what you have done will never ever die.  You may as well all delete your characters and take this as a lesson learned. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :asshole --><img src=http://216.40.249.192/s/contrib/geno/asshole2.gif ALT=":asshole"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
